OL,6,GThe National Union of Journalists
OL,7,Gsays it will ballot members for
OL,8,Gindustrial action following a
OL,9,Gdecision by BBC management to abandon
OL,10,Gtalks and press ahead with changes to
OL,11,Gthe BBC Radio Foyle schedule.
OL,13,FLast November, the BBC announced
OL,14,Fplans to axe the weekday Breakfast
OL,15,FShow on BBC Radio Foyle, as well as
OL,16,Fhourly news bulletins and the 30-
OL,17,Fminute lunchtime news programme.
OL,18,F Eight journalist positions were to
OL,19,Fbe removed from the station.
OL,21,FEarlier today, revised proposals were
OL,22,Fmade public:
OL,3,CNUJ to ballot members for industrial
OL,4,Caction over Foyle changes
