OL,6,
OL,7,F The Breakfast Show is to continue,
OL,8,Fbut reduced from 2 hours to 30
OL,9,Fminutes.
OL,10,F Hourly news bulletins are to be
OL,11,Fretained.
OL,12,F The lunchtime news programme will
OL,13,Fstill be axed.
OL,14,F The BBC says it expects staffing
OL,15,Flevels to remain unchanged: "This
OL,16,Fincludes some new roles to help
OL,17,Fdeliver local and region-wide
OL,18,Fprogramming across the BBC's
OL,19,Fservices."
OL,20,F Production of some BBC Radio Ulster
OL,21,Fprogrammes would move to BBC Radio
OL,22,FFoyle (the Hugo Duncan afternoon show
OL,23,Fand evening programmes, including
OL,24,Fthose presented by Ralph McLean and
OL,25,FEve Blair).
OL,3,CNUJ to ballot members for industrial
OL,4,Caction over Foyle changes
